## Deployment

### Web (Vercel)
- Root Directory blank in Vercel UI; `vercel.json` at repo root is source of truth
- `next` must be in root `package.json` devDeps — Vercel uses it for framework detection
- Prisma uses WASM engine + custom webpack loader (`apps/web/prisma-wasm-loader.js`)
- `packages/db/src/index.ts` uses pg Pool with `DIRECT_URL` (not pgbouncer) for driver adapter
- SSL: `rejectUnauthorized: false` (Supabase CA not in Node trust store)
- Student layout auto-creates student record if Clerk webhook missed it (prevents redirect loop)
- `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` on root layout — prevents Clerk prerender crash
- `outputFileTracingRoot` at top-level of next.config (NOT inside experimental) — Next.js 15 change

### AI Service (Railway)
- Root Directory in Railway: `apps/ai-service`
- Watch Paths: `apps/ai-service/**`
- Port: 8000
- All routes protected by `X-Service-Key` header (checked against `AI_SERVICE_SECRET_KEY`)
- Health check: GET /health → `{"status": "ok", "service": "compass-ai"}`
- Was failing to deploy due to next@14.2.29 vulnerability — fixed by upgrade to v15

### Required Vercel Env Vars
DATABASE_URL, DIRECT_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY, CLERK_SECRET_KEY,
CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET, UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL, UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN, QSTASH_TOKEN,
QSTASH_CURRENT_SIGNING_KEY, QSTASH_NEXT_SIGNING_KEY, AI_SERVICE_URL (no trailing slash),
AI_SERVICE_SECRET_KEY, NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL

### Required Railway Env Vars
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, VOYAGE_API_KEY, DATABASE_URL (direct, port 5432), AI_SERVICE_SECRET_KEY,
APP_URL (Vercel domain, for CORS)

